Common.LongDescription.Common.Text: CBRE is pleased to offer for sale a total of ± 5.05 acres for multifamily residential uses located in The Meadows, a 420 acre master-planned community, nestled in the Rosewood neighborhood of Saskatoon, SK. When completed, The Meadows will feature 2,200+ new homes and 65 acres of parks, ponds and pathways. Within the Meadows, lies the Meadows Market, a retail power centre with Costco, boutiques, restaurants, and many more  amenities. Overall, the site is well situated within Saskatoon and is a short 7 minute drive to the city center.

CBRE is pleased to offer for sale a total of ± 5.05 acres for multifamily residential uses located in The Meadows, a 420 acre master-planned community, nestled in the Rosewood neighborhood of Saskatoon, SK. When completed, The Meadows will feature 2,200+ new homes and 65 acres of parks, ponds and pathways. Within the Meadows, lies the Meadows Market, a retail power centre with Costco, boutiques, restaurants, and many more  amenities. Overall, the site is well situated within Saskatoon and is a short 7 minute drive to the city center.

The subject 40-acre parcel is located 1.6 kms south of Saskatoon city limits in the RM of Corman Park. The Grasswood subdivision is located immediately north and west. The proximity to Saskatoon’s southern boundary, this land would be ideal for residential acreage development. There is a single-family home in good condition on the southwest corner of the subject parcel, surrounded by mature deciduous trees and shrubs.

CBRE Limited is pleased to offer for sale a total of ±86.61 acres for residential uses that includes 46 serviced lots (collectively “the Offering”) in the northern portion of the Kensington neighbourhood located in the City of Saskatoon, Saskatchewan. The development lands, which comprise of ±86.61 acres, are designated for a mix of low and medium density residential uses and the 46 lots range in size from 28 feet to 54 feet.

CBRE is pleased to offer 160 acres located on the East side Range Road 3063 north of 33rd Street West in the Rural Municipality of Corman Park, Saskatchewan. The land is currently leased to a farmer for a grain growing operation and located within the Saskatoon Planning District, an area jointly managed by the R. M. of Corman Park and the City of Saskatoon. It is expected that at some date in the future the boundary of the City of Saskatoon may be extended to include this quarter section.
